      • JSContext

        public JSContext(java.lang.Class<?> iface)
          throws JSException
        Creates a JavaScript context, and defines the global object with interface 'iface'. This object must implement 'iface'. The methods in 'iface' will be exposed to the JavaScript environment.
        Parameters:
        iface - The interface to expose to JavaScript
        Throws:
        JSException

      • persistObject

        public void persistObject(JSObject obj)
        Keeps a reference to an object in this context. This is used so that only one Java object instance wrapping a JavaScript object is maintained at any time. This way, local variables in the Java object will stay wrapped around all returns of the same instance. This is handled by JSObject, and should not need to be called by clients.
        Parameters:
        obj - The object with which to associate with this context

      • finalizeObject

        public void finalizeObject(JSObject obj)
        Removes a reference to an object in this context. Should only be used from the 'finalize' object method. This is handled by JSObject, and should not need to be called by clients.
        Parameters:
        obj -
